>The door bursts open as you hit the bottom
>That’s it
>Dead end
>You spin around and your heart stops
>Crawling down the stairs is a ghost-white werewolf, chuckling with that feminine, yet malicious voice
>She’s covered in bloody bandages and the tattered remains of a regal dress
>Her lips are pulled back to show her pearly fangs, and her crimson eyes are full of hunger
>She rises to two legs, a good head taller than you
>”I want you to scream, so I can hear that musical gurgle when I rip open your throat.”
>She takes a step forward with each of your retreating steps, until you’re backed against the concrete wall
>There’s a bone-chilling groan at your feet
>The werewolf slams her front paws down, as though preparing to pounce
>The floor gives away all around you
>You plummet into the darkness
>The last sight you see is the silhouette of the werewolf looming over you

>You don’t know how long you’ve been out for, but your head still throbs
>You also don’t know if the fall is part of the attraction, but now you’re on a neat pile of sheets and broken furniture
