>”Good, uh, sorry. We woke up back at the entrance and there were rats everywhere and she was still chasing us. Glad you made it out.”
>Thanks guys
>You send out a ride request, and within minutes an old man with some uncomfortably sagging skin pulls up in an unremarkable sedan
>You drop your phone into your pocket and feel something out of place
>Crinkling?
>Digging inside, you find a weathered looking envelope
>[To Anon]
>That’s not unsettling at all...
>You tear open the envelope, which shreds into a fine dust
>Sorry about the mess, Mr. Driver
>[Dear Anon]
>[Congratulations to you on your successful trial through the night! Very few make it as far as you have, believe it or not.]
